HEADWORD: Rashly
<hw>Rash"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a rash manner; with
precipitation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that doth anything <qex>rashly</qex>, must do it willingly; for
he was free to deliberate or not.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rashness</ent>⟦br⟧
